==English==
===Etymology===
{{Gr.}} ''tri-'' three; ''meros'' part
===Noun===
'''trimer'''

#{{chemistry}} A molecule consisting of a chain of three parts, so called [[monomer]]s. A trimer is formed by joining three identical molecules.

